Clinical presentation of COVID-19 may range from mild (81%) to severe (14%) and critical (5%)14
, (Fig. 1
). Typical signs and symptoms of COVID-19 include the following: fever (87.9%), dry cough (67.7%), fatigue (38.1%), sputum production (33.4%), shortness of breath (18.6%), sore throat (13.9%), headache (13.6%), myalgia or arthralgia (14.8%), chills (11.4%), nausea or vomiting (5.0%), nasal congestion (4.8%), diarrhea (3.7%), hemoptysis (0.9%), and conjunctival congestion (0.8%).15
